The Anambra Government has earmarked six billion naira for the construction of the Anambra State International Cargo Airport at Umueri, near Awka. <img class="alignnone wp-image-1261530 size-large" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=640%2C497&#038;ssl=1" alt="Anambra earmarks N6bn for cargo airport" width="640" height="497" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=1024%2C795&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=300%2C233&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=768%2C596&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=58%2C45&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=250%2C194&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=167%2C130&amp;ssl=1 167w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?resize=560%2C435&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anam-port1-1.png?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Gov. Willie Obiano made the disclosure at the presentation of the state’s 2020 budget to the state’s assembly on Thursday in Awka. He announced that a total of N22.2 billion was estimated for the construction of roads and bridges, while N6 .98 billion was set aside for implementation of strategic initiatives in the health sector. Obiano, who later hosted stakeholders at the Government Lodge in Amawbia, near Awka, said his administration decided to invest in the airport to actualise the promise he made during 2017 governorship campaign. The governor said that constructing an international airport in the state would boost economic development and increase the income base of the state. He said that critics of his administration airport would be shocked at the pace of work at the airport’s site after the rainy season. Obiano, who also spoke extensively on what his administration was doing in the health sector, urged residents of the state to embrace the state’s health insurance scheme. “A lot of testimonies are being given on the state health insurance scheme, due to the effective nature of the scheme. “I am appealing to the people of Anambra State and to non-natives residing in our state, to register with the scheme because of the immense benefits of the scheme,’’ he said. Vanguard, Nigeria News Awka—Governor Willie Obiano of Anambra State has promised to ensure immediate commencement of work on the Umueri International Cargo Airport with a view to making the airport ready for use in three years. April 12, 2017 In "News" A former governor of Central Bank of Nigeria, Prof. Chukwuma Soludo, has commended Gov. Willie Obiano of Anambra over his achievements in the area of economy within three years in office. March 18, 2017 In "News" THE Anambra State branch of the Association of Professional Bodies in Nigeria (APBN), said yesterday that it was unhappy with the slow pace of work at the site of the International Cargo Airport project in Umuleri in Anambra East local government area being executed by the state government. August 4, 2018 In "News"